<section class="section">
  <p class="section-label">Why Emboss</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">What changes when<br>you add a finish</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">Frappe Gantt nailed the engine. Emboss adds the finish it deserves.</p>
  <div class="compare-grid">
    <div class="compare-card before">
      <div class="compare-label">Frappe Gantt alone</div>
      <h4>Flat bars, basic popup</h4>
      <p>Functional but generic. Every implementation looks the same. Limited customization without forking. No sidebar, no phases, no visual hierarchy.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="compare-card after">
      <div class="compare-label">With Emboss</div>
      <h4>Glass bars, extension system</h4>
      <p>Progress markers, drag handles, dependency arrows on hover. Sidebar with phase grouping, collapse, rail mode. Dark theme. Dense mode. All composable through extensions.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

